RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 6 1/2F Turf CR: 91. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 36000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING $50,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Horses Entered For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 10 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EL ORO (FR) broke well then ceded command to TIGERHON (FR) early, was cautious going up inside the leader leaving the backstretch and steadied into the turn, moved up to challenge along the rail on the turn, put a head in front in front and got bumped in upper stretch, battled through the final furlong and dug in to prevail. TIGERHON (FR) hit the inner side of the stall leaving the gate, moved up quickly to clear, dueled with EL ORO (FR) on the turn, lost command in upper stretch and drifted in to bump that rival shortly after, fought gamely through the final furlong and was edged for the victory. BATTLE CALL settled at the back early, raced along the rail into the turn, swung out past the quarter pole and into the lane, closed fast from the middle of the track but ran out of time. GREENBOW was off slow to begin, chased while saving ground through the turn, angled out in upper stretch to take aim at the top pair but finished evenly in the late stages. J D'S RUDE BOY stalked the top pair outside a rival into the turn, chased three then two wide around the bend and could not respond when called upon. MISSED CALL tracked two wide into the turn, spun three wide into the lane and failed to rally.

By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, May 25, 2023, closed with 10 or by Supplementary nomination of $4,000 at time of entry. $1,500 to enter and an additional $1,500 to start with $200,000 guaranteed of which $120,000 to the winner, $40,000 to second, $24,000 to third, $12,000 to fourth and $4,000 to fifth. 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Grade I or Grade II Stake at One Mile or Over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of a Graded Stake at One Mile or over allowed 4 lb s. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WINDOW SHOPPING stalked between rivals early, coaxed through the far turn, angled in leaving the bend, tipped back out and bid between foes in upper stretch, raced on even terms into deep stretch and proved best late. LILY POO got crowded between rivals prior to the first turn, chased three wide around that bend at the back, was on the move three deep through the far turn, bid outside rivals in the lane, fought three deep into deep stretch and got outkicked by the top pair.
